race.description: Chery Checkered Flag Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: BLAZING FUTURE (1) has settled at the tail of the field then made plenty of late ground to fill minor placings in his two runs to date, both over 1300m. Crying out for this trip and will prove very tough to hold out. LADY YARROW (6) recorded her fifth minor placing from eight starts when a distant third over this trip at Hawkesbury last time out. Has been up for a while but continues to deliver. Well drawn and should be in the money again. G'DAY AUSBRED (3) battled on okay after showing early pace on debut recently. Less pressure today over the longer journey so should give a great sight. SOVERATO (10) finished the race off well on debut last start so an extra 200m looks the right option.
